Value.SimpleValue: A numerical amount (typically a currency amount), expressed as a decimal value.

ComplexValue.doc:name: Amount
ComplexValue.doc:description: A numerical amount (typically a currency amount), expressed as a decimal value.

Value.SimpleValue: A value expressed in terms of one hundredths of a percent, i.e. 5 means 5 basis points (bp) or 0.05%.

ComplexValue.doc:name: BasisPoints
ComplexValue.doc:description: A value expressed in terms of one hundredths of a percent, i.e. 5 means 5 basis points (bp) or 0.05%.

Value.SimpleValue: The value (expressed in currency units) per basis point change in the underlying rate. Typically used for expressing sensitivity to interest rate chages ("IR delta" risk, "rho" risk).

ComplexValue.doc:name: BasisPointValue
ComplexValue.doc:description: The value (expressed in currency units) per basis point change in the underlying rate. Typically used for expressing sensitivity to interest rate chages ("IR delta" risk, "rho" risk).

Value.SimpleValue: The Basis Point Value (BPV) (expressed in currency units per basis point) per basis point change in the underlying rate. Typically used for expressing second order sensitivity to interest rate changes (IR "gamma" risk, "convexity").

ComplexValue.doc:name: BasisPointValuePerBasisPoint
ComplexValue.doc:description: The Basis Point Value (BPV) (expressed in currency units per basis point) per basis point change in the underlying rate. Typically used for expressing second order sensitivity to interest rate changes (IR "gamma" risk, "convexity").

ComplexValue.doc:name: BBL
ComplexValue.doc:additionalInformation: Assumed to have the same (volume) value for all commodities: 1 BBL = 42 USGAL = 158.987 L = 35 imperial GAL. For oil, volume measured at 14.696 lb/in^2 (101.325 kPa) pressure and temperature 60 °F (15.6 °C).
